The government will spend Sh300 million to connect 250 households with electricity in Nyaribari Chache constituency, Kisii county, Energy CS Charles Keter has said.On Friday, he said the households will be connected within two weeks to cushion residents from spending money in buying kerosene.Seventy per cent of the households in the area will be connected with electricity by June 2017, up from 30 percent in 2013, Keter said.The CS urged Kenyans to take advantage of access to power either in their homesteads or shopping centers to invest in income generating projects to boost their well being.